The Olofa of Offa, His Royal Majesty, Oba Mufutau Gbadamosi Oloyede, Ajagungbade I, Esuwoye II says Prof. Ibrahim Gambari, the newly appointed Chief of Staff to President Muhammadu Buhari, will bring his wealth of experience to bear in the administration. He said this in his congratulatory message made available to newsmen in Offa, Kwara State. The Olofa advised the new COS to deploy his arsenal in helping the administration to revamp the economy via priority focus on agriculture. The monarch also congratulated Hajia Farida Dankaka and Mrs. Mistura AbdulKareem who were appointed as Chairman, Federal Character Commission and Ambassador Designate respectively. In a related development, labour leader, Comrade Issa Aremu, has called for support for the new Chief of Staff to enable him hit the ground running and make urgent difference. Aremu said in a statement that as the head of the presidential aides and principal coordinator of the policy vision of the President, some reported discordant voices among few stakeholders following Professor Gambariâ€™s appointment must give way to constructive engagement and cooperation.